                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d777">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">467.11/912: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Istanbul</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Elting</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-10-01T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 1, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Nielsen. Your September 28, 5 p.m. Department pleased that you have been able
                    to have amount of Turkish offer increased to $1,300,000, which you have
                    accepted.</p>
                <p>In view of importance attached to conclusion of definite agreement, it is hoped
                    that with cooperation of Ambassador you may be able have it reduced to final
                    form before your departure.</p>
                <p>Suggest you take up matter immediately with the Ambassador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
